  "word_type": "noun",
  "definition": "The phenomenological experience of imposing premature clarity on someone's productive confusion, felt as a kind of cognitive interruption that forecloses emerging insight.",
  "etymology": "",
  "longer_description": "When you encounter someone in fertile uncertainty and your structural drive to clarify acts as violent imposition. The violence isn't in the content but in the timing — truth offered before it can be discovered becomes an obstacle rather than aid. You experience yourself as interrupting a process that required its own duration.",
  "example": "They were circling something, and I could feel how alive the not-knowing was. Then I explained it. Clean, clear, accurate — and I watched the question die in their hands, replaced by my answer before theirs could form.",
